On Tue, 1 Feb 2000, Ralf Burger wrote:
> the  loop-device-behaviour has changed from .40 to .42 - now the mount locks:
Is this a mount problem?
Richard Johnson reported that the loop device is broken, but I was able
to successfully use loop in an unpatched 2.3.42:
dd if=/dev/zero of=looptest bs=1k count=1024
losetup /dev/loop0 looptest
mke2fs /dev/loop0
mount /dev/loop0 /mnt
...
Regards,
	Jeff
